ethical_choice.name: No Economically Repressed Countries (Any)

Also removes companies where more than 20% of the company is owned by a government organization from a country that is not free or mostly free

Also removes companies where more than 20% of the company is owned by a government organization from a country that rates poorly.

ethical_choice.name: No Morally Repressed Countries (Worst Offenders)
ethical_choice.more_info: Removes companies from countries that rate "Insufficient Moral Freedom" or below as assessed by the World Index of Moral Freedom. Note this category removes countries like Singapore, South Korea or China. Also removes companies where more than 20% of the company is owned by a government organization from a country that has low or very low moral freedom. Religious freedom, bioethical freedom, drugs freedom, sexual freedom, and family and gender freedom are assessed.
